title: $:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/readme
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! What it does

A keyboard-driven cascading command palette for TiddlyWiki. Hit one hotkey (default: ''Ctrl-Space'') to open. Type to filter a stage. ''→'' (Right-arrow) drills into a stage. ''Space'' opens the action menu on typed rows (works on containers too). ''Esc'' walks one stage back, ''Shift-Esc'' closes from any depth. ''Enter'' fires the selected action. Domain plugins (e.g. `rimir/orga-palette`) extend the palette by shipping declarative ''entry'' and ''action'' tiddlers — no widget code required.

! Key features

* ''Cascading stages'' — every drill pushes a new stage; ArrowLeft / Esc pops one stage at any depth, Shift-Esc closes from any depth. Breadcrumb shows where you are.
* ''Declarative protocol'' — adding a new cascade is one tiddler. Tag, fields, done.
* ''Generic engine'' — no domain knowledge baked in. Same widget serves any catalogue plugin.
* ''Multi-view root menu'' — switch between ''Entries'' / ''All tiddlers'' / ''By namespace'' / ''By parent'' / ''Hybrid'' / ''By date'' views from a pill strip above the input. Each view is a composition of one or more ''structure layers'' (`ca-view-layers` lists them) — each layer declaring its own `roots` + `children` filters, row decorations, and optional `row-entity-type` for context-action drilling. A focusable ''Structure'' strip below the view pills makes the active view's composition externally visible: compact by default (one summary row with view name + layer-count + view-scoped pills), expandable on Enter/Space/→ to a full stacked layout (view-scoped header + one mini-row per layer with all primitive pills). Arrow keys navigate the expanded grid; each focused pill renders contextual help into the details drawer. Entries can opt into per-view placement via `ca-position-<view-slug>` fields. Add your own views as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/view` and your own layers as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/structure-layer`.
* ''Grouping axes'' — any structure-layer can declare a chain of ''axes'' that bucket the layer's source set at the top of the descent: year → month → day, status → year, prefix → tag, anything you can write as a one-filter derive-key. Axes ''compose with'' the layer's recursive `children` filter — so the same layer can be pure grouping (axes only), today's recursive tree (children only), or both (bucket the forest roots, then descend each). Edit chains live from the Structure strip: yellow ''by'' / ''→'' pills in each layer's mini-row, ''+'' pill to append, Backspace to remove, Shift-←/→ to reorder, Enter to swap. Ship axes as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/axis` — `ca-axis-key` is a one-line filter mapping rows to bucket keys.
* ''Leader keys'' — type a single char and idle for 200ms to fire a shortcut: `x` clears all filter+visibility pills, `>` opens a tree-picker that commits a path as a title-prefix filter, `s` saves the current state as a named preset, `r` jumps focus to the preset strip. Every visible leader is also surfaced as a pill in the ''Leader'' strip above the input, so the available gestures are discoverable without prior knowledge — Tab into the strip, ←/→ to select, ↵/Space to fire. Leaders may be view-scoped via ''`ca-leader-views`'' (a filter producing view titles) — empty / missing means global. Author your own as tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/leader`.
* ''Presets'' — save any combination of active view + filter pills + visibility pills under a name; replay later by picking the preset's pill. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/preset`.
* ''Filter strip'' — type `/foo`, `prefix:work/`, `#tag`, `@<tiddler>` to stack ''filter'' pills that narrow every result list. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/filter`.
* ''Visibility strip'' — type `hide:appify` to hide entries by group, or Shift-DEL on a root row to hide a single entry. Tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/visibility`. Ctrl-DEL clears both filter and visibility strips.
* ''Filter substitution'' — `<<query>>`, `<<picked>>`, `<<parent-picked>>`, `<<context-tiddler>>` available in every filter and action. Filter/visibility expressions also see `<arg>` and `<<arg>>`. Inside a preview-bearing subtree, `<<stage-preview-context>>` exposes the entity the side preview is pinned to.
* ''Sticky context'' — pin one or more tiddlers (Space → ''Pin to context'', or type ''`+<title>`'' + Enter for a one-handed pin) and they appear as the ''Context'' pill strip + the `<<sticky-context-list>>` / `<<sticky-context-count>>` variables exposed to every filter/action scope. ''Page-session only'' — reload clears it (capture as a preset if you need cross-reload memory). Views opt in to narrowing by referencing the variable in their layer filters AND declaring ''`ca-view-context-aware: yes`'' to paint a small badge when context is non-empty. Generic verbs (Pin / Unpin / Clear) ship here; workflow-specific verbs (call, meeting, focus) belong in a sibling plugin like ''`rimir/worga`''.
* ''Row icons'' — small glyphs in a footer strip below tiddler-bearing rows, surfacing affordances on the row's backing tiddler. Shipped: a ''🌐'' glyph appears on any tiddler whose configured URL field(s) carry an http/https/ftp/mailto/tel value (default field: ''`url`'' — configurable via ''`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/url-fields`''). ''Alt-↵'' on a row with at least one icon (or clicking the glyph directly) fires the primary icon's action — for ''🌐'' that opens the URL in a new browser tab; ''Ctrl-Alt-↵'' fires the icon's secondary action — for ''🌐'' that copies the URL to the clipboard. Author your own via tiddlers tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/row-icon`''.
* ''Actionable-row indicator'' — every row whose tiddler has at least one applicable action (via catalogue / configured-field bridge / `ca-applies` filter) gets a thin indigo bar at its leading edge (`rcp-row-actionable` class) AND a right-edge ''`→N`'' badge counting the available actions. Lets you scan ↑/↓ down a long list and see where Space will actually open something — no speculative keystrokes. Three discovery paths unioned: ''catalogue'' (action `ca-entity-type` matches the row's bound type — set by `ca-layer-row-entity-type` on the emitting layer); ''configured-field bridge'' (when an installed plugin sets `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/entity-type-field` to a field name, e.g. `kind` ships it as `kind.type` — action `ca-entity-type: <X>` then auto-matches any row whose tiddler has `<configured-field>: <X>`); ''filter'' (action declares `ca-applies` — filter evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` = row title, non-empty result = applies). All three further narrowed by per-action `ca-action-when`. Per-view opt-out via `ca-view-show-action-preview: no`.
* ''Row labels'' — switch the displayed name of every data row from a single-select pill strip below the view strip. Pre-row-labels a kind-instance showed its caption in catalogue drills but its raw title in ''All tiddlers'' / ''By namespace'' (each view chose its own `ca-view-row-name`). The active pill (a filter evaluated per row with `<currentTiddler>`) overrides that uniformly. Ships with three pills — ''Title'', ''Caption'', and ''Caption → Title'' (default, captioned tiddlers caption-first, everything else by title). Extensible: tag your own tiddlers with `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/row-label`, declare `ca-row-label-filter`, sort with `ca-order`. Active pick persists across reload (`$:/state/rimir/cascade-palette/row-label`). Static palette entries / actions keep their explicit `ca-name`; only data rows are overridden.
* ''Side preview pane'' — right-column pane that opens when the user drills into a row whose menu declared a preview (or whose context matches a tagged auto-attach candidate). Two registration mechanisms work in parallel: ''per-menu'' — an entry/action sets ''`ca-preview-template`'' (+ optional ''`ca-preview-context`'' filter / ''`ca-preview-title`'' caption / ''`ca-preview-name`'' pill label), explicit and pinned at drill-time; ''tag-based'' — any tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview`'' is a candidate whose ''`ca-preview-applies`'' filter is evaluated against the active context, auto-attaching whenever it matches (no per-menu wiring needed). When two or more candidates apply at the same context, a pill row appears at the top of the pane — ←/→ when the pane has focus cycles between them (also click). The cascade visually shrinks to 50% on the left; the pane stays mounted while the registering stage (or any deeper one) is on the stack, then disappears when the user pops past. Use it to live-render a form for the kind being edited, a chart of the data being filtered, etc. Distinct from the ''detail'' drawer (the Ctrl-hold / always-on row below the menu), which is bound to the selected row.
* ''Keyboard-first'' — Up/Down to select, Tab to cycle sections (input → preset → visibility → filter → view → structure → leader → menu → detail → preview), Shift-Tab to jump between the pill-group and the main group, Esc to walk one stage back (closes only at root from input), Shift-Esc to close from any depth, Enter to fire. ''→'' drills (descend tree containers / open the action menu on typed catalogue leaves); ''Space'' opens the action menu on ''any'' tiddler row whose actions match via `ca-applies` — works in tree views (By namespace, By parent, Hybrid), not only in the catalogue. Left/Right inside the input preserve normal cursor behaviour. ''Type-ahead'' — start typing a printable character from any section and focus jumps back to the input with the character appended, so you never have to Tab back just to keep filtering.

! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki ≥ 5.4.0

! Quick start

Install the plugin, restart. Ctrl-Space opens the palette. Out of the box you get four demo entries (Open Control Panel, Save Wiki, Advanced Search, Recent Tiddlers…) so you can confirm it's working. The real value is in shipping your own ''entry'' and ''action'' tiddlers — see the [[Documentation]] tab for the protocol.

To rebind, edit the tiddler `$:/config/shortcuts/rimir-cascade-palette-open`.

! Extending: the action-tiddler protocol

* ''Entry tiddlers'' — root-stage menu items. Tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`.
* ''Action tiddlers'' — what appears in the action menu for a picked entity. Tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action`, scoped via `ca-entity-type` field.

Each tiddler declares whether it's a ''leaf'' (fires actions on Enter and closes) or a ''drill'' (pushes a new stage). Cascades form an implicit graph: a drill from type A → type B is just a tiddler with `ca-entity-type: A` and `ca-next-entity-type: B`. Add a new edge by writing one tiddler.

See the Documentation tab's ''Protocol'' section for full schema and worked examples.
